Healthworkers' union, Hospersa and its federation, Fedusa is calling for Tygerberg Hospital in the Western Cape to shut its doors. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Two unions are calling for Tygerberg Hospital in the Western Cape to shut its doors. They claim the hospital is being reckless and is in violation of COVID-19 protocols. Trade unions Hospersa and Fedusa say they've conducted a preliminary inspection and are convinced the hospital has the potential of becoming a major breeding ground for COVID-19 infections. READ: Western Cape puts plan in place to curb spread of COVID-19 “Hospersa is alarmed by the Occupational Health and Safety contraventions and disregard of COVID-19 protocols at Tygerberg Hospital,” said Hospersa WC provincial chairperson, Gerald Lotriet. “We were shaken by the increasing number of positive COVID-19 cases amongst the hospital’s staff and instituted a preliminary investigation. READ: COVID-19: Tygerberg Hospital workers test positive "The investigation revealed that the hospital is becoming a breeding ground for COVID-19 due to the lack of preventative measures being taken to stop the spread of this deadly virus,” added Lotriet. The unions are now calling on the Labour Department to shut down the institution and for an investigation to be conducted. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.